The paper deals with solving inverse imaging problems using deep learning techniques, specifically denoising neural networks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of optimization algorithms and their parameters, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with signal processing and information theory, which are covered by the information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses numerical analysis and optimization, which are covered by the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category.
